<font color="#FF0000">CALL ME DOC CRAZY</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 12  0:59:44 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I was not in country, in the jungle with you, yet now, I know what it was..<br><br>
I did not hump a 80lb pack back nor clean a M-16 in the dark, but now I know what it is.<br><br>
I did not try and stuff someone's guts back in a impossible<br>
stomach hit, but now I know what it must have felt like.<br><br>
I did not safe a soul, though I tried war earlier up the line, by trying to stop the trains....<br><br>
I did not hose down police cars, not beat my wife, nor<br>
raise my bottle higher and higher, yet I know the cost..<br><br>
All I did, as I posted, was protest. protest with all my<br>
heart, the foolhearty war that took 56,000 of my generation,<br>
56,000 of my brothers, and a few sisters, for naught.  For Naught? No. For the right of those FUCKING POLITICIANS in Washington to keep on doing it, generation after generation, and they get a paycheck bonus each year to boot.  We got no benefits, No G.I.Bill (unless you are a vet, and not like me, a C.O.), but we got plenty of refugee's.  You guys gut a Memorial Wall to shut you up, to trick you into silent agreement.  The protestors got nothing.  McNamara finally agreed that the Protestors Were Right, but only because he is about to meet his maker.  Had he been a young politician, he would have continued the lie.<br><br>
So where are WE all now? Veterans and protestors? At least we are alive.  And at least we know that OUR government lies to us whenever it is convienient, and that it will throw aside our buddies, our compradriots whenever it needs to. How many Americans were left behind in WW2? How many left to the Communists in the Korean War? How man in Viet Nam? The numbers make me want to puke.<br><br>
So, Wake up brothers. Wake up Sisters. Bill and Hillary are not our friends. Nor is any politician. Nor is the Militia's and their dastardly deed in Oklahoma.  Where is America, I cry, in the dark of night. Where is my country, home of the free and the brave, in the dead of night.<br><br>
I fear it is lost, lost as my soul feels, adrift in this sea of political correctness and global warming bullshit.  Adrift among enemies.  Jesus, is this how it ends, not with a bang, but a fart?<br><br>
doc spatz
